I'll help you get started with exploring the codebase. Let me first check what's available in the current directory.

```bash
ls -la
```

```bash
pwd
```

```bash
find . -type f -name "*.py" -o -name "*.js" -o -name "*.ts" -o -name "*.java" -o -name "*.cpp" -o -name "*.c" -o -name "*.h" -o -name "*.go" -o -name "*.rs" -o -name "*.php" -o -name "*.rb" -o -name "*.swift" -o -name "*.kt" -o -name "*.scala" -o -name "*.m" -o -name "*.sh" -o -name "*.pl" -o -name "*.lua" -o -name "*.r" -o -name "*.sql" -o -name "*.md" -o -name "*.txt" -o -name "*.json" -o -name "*.yaml" -o -name "*.yml" -o -name "*.xml" -o -name "*.html" -o -name "*.css" -o -name "*.dockerfile" -o -name "*Dockerfile*" -o -name "*Makefile*" -o -name "*.mk" -o -name "*.cmake" -o -name "*.toml" -o -name "*.ini" -o -name "*.conf" -o -name "*.cfg" -o -name "*.properties" | head -20
```

Let me also check if there are any hidden directories or git repositories:

```bash
ls -la | grep -E "^d"
```

```bash
find . -name ".git" -type d 2>/dev/null
```

```bash
find . -name ".svn" -type d 2>/dev/null
```

```bash
find . -name ".hg" -type d 2>/dev/null
```
